  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dba\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The supply of food to inpatients is also limited",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to rising food prices and gas crisis, it is reported that providing food to the inpatients in hospitals has also become a problem.",
        "This situation has arisen in Colombo National Hospital, Lady Ridgeway Children's Hospital, Maharagama Apeksha Hospital, Kalubowila Teaching Hospital and many other district and regional hospitals.",
        "A spokesman for the Colombo National Hospital said that the food provided to patients and hospital staff admitted for treatment has been restricted for about four months.",
        "The spokesman said that at present the patients were being given a diet consisting of only two types of vegetables and that they were not being given the nutritious food they needed.",
        "The spokesman said that except for two curries such as pumpkin, dhal, potatoes, mango and carrot, the serving of fish slices or eggs as well as desserts such as fruit and yoghurt given to patients earlier has been stopped.",
        "Patients with diabetes and kidney disease are not given a proper diet and health workers are served rice with coconut sambol, cucumbers, potatoes and pumpkin, he said.",
        "The spokesman said that the Ministry of Health has been informed but no action has been taken.",
        "It is also reported that mothers in the maternity wards of some hospitals are being given coconut sambol, potato curd etc. and cereals are not being provided.",
        "Due to the difficulties in providing transportation facilities due to the current fuel crisis, it has become a problem to bring food from home to the patients who are receiving residential treatment in hospitals far away from home.",
        "Due to this, it is reported that the amount of food provided by the hospitals is not sufficient to provide the patients."
      ],
